# 📝 Smart Notes Semantic Search

## 🎯 Project Name
Smart Notes Semantic Search using Endee Vector Database

## 🖥️ Existing System
Traditional note apps use keyword search.
Example: Search "sad" → only finds notes with exact word "sad".
Missing notes that say "terrible day" or "feeling low".

## 🎯 Main Objective
Build a semantic search system that finds notes by MEANING
not just exact keywords using AI embeddings and Endee
vector database.

## 🥅 Goal
User types "feeling upset" → system finds
"I had a terrible day at office" ✅
Even though the words are completely different!

##  What is Implemented
- 10 sample notes loaded into Endee vector database
- AI converts text to vectors using sentence-transformers
- Semantic search finds similar meaning notes
- User can add their own notes
- Simple clean frontend UI

##  System Architecture
User Query
    ↓
Frontend (HTML + JS)
    ↓
Backend API (FastAPI + Python)
    ↓
Sentence Transformer (converts text → vector)
    ↓
Endee Vector Database (finds similar vectors)
    ↓
Returns matching notes 

## 🛠️ Tech Stack
| Layer      | Technology                    |
|------------|-------------------------------|
| Vector DB  | Endee (endee-io/endee)        |
| Embeddings | sentence-transformers         |
| Backend    | FastAPI (Python)              |
| Frontend   | HTML + CSS + JavaScript       |
| Deployment | Render (backend) + Netlify    |

